  <title>2.3 Part-Editor:</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Editor<keyword>Part</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Part-Editor</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">About the Part-Editor</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;"><image src="2r.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text>Part-Editor </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Use the <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor</text> to add and edit sketch-elements, sketch-loops, and dimensions in the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text> and <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> you add.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Text">When you are using the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, and you want to edit a different </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, you must first close the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor </text><text styleclass="Body Text">to return to the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. Then you can select the other </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> and start the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> again.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-How-to-start-the-Part-Editor">How to start the Part-Editor</link></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Close-Part-Editor">How to close the Part-Editor</link></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-WhatisGeometryUsedfor">Why edit a Part?</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Interface2">Notes<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="Element-Header">Base-Parts</text> and <text styleclass="Interface2">Sketch-Elements</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Before you can <text styleclass="Body Text">add a joint between the </text><text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> and a </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, you</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">must</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> edit the </text><text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> to add to it a minimum of one(1) sketch-element.</text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">You can, of course, add any number of sketch-elements to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName">The first sketch-element in the <text styleclass="Element-Header">Base-Part</text>?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We always add a <text styleclass="Element">Line </text>as the first sketch-element to the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text>. </para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName">Why? </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">A </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> gives the most flexibility when we need to join other </text><text styleclass="Element">Parts</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">We can </text>select the <text styleclass="Element">Line&apos;s</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> and/or <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> to add <text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joints</text>, and the <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> to add <text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joints</text>, between the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text> and a different <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We can also reference the <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> and/or the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> or <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> to add a <text styleclass="Element">Motion-Dimension FB</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, and</text> so define the motion of a <text styleclass="Element">Rocker</text> and/or <text styleclass="Element">Slider </text>relative to the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Part-Editor workspace</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="1" style="cell-padding:0px;">
